        <p class="text-lg text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">
          We built a scoring system for agent-native tools. Before we
          launched, we scored ourselves.
          <strong class="text-slate-200">3.5/10 (L1 Emerging)</strong>.
          This is the full breakdown.
        </p>
      </header>

      <section class="mb-10 rounded-xl border border-amber/20 bg-elevated p-6">
        <p class="text-xs font-mono font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.22em] text-amber mb-3">
          Historical baseline
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
          This March 11 post is the original pre-launch baseline self-assessment.
          For the later fuller public self-assessment and current reference point,
          read{" "}
          <a href="/blog/we-scored-ourselves" class="text-amber hover:underline underline-offset-2">
            We Scored Ourselves
          </a>
          , where Rhumb scores 6.8/10 and every remaining gap is still published.
        </p>
      </section>

      <div class="prose-rhumb" set:html={htmlContent} />

      <section class="mt-16 rounded-[28px] border border-emerald-500/20 bg-emerald-500/5 p-6">
        <div class="text-[11px] font-mono uppercase tracking-[0.24em] text-emerald-300 mb-3">Next honest step</div>
        <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-2xl text-slate-100 mb-3 tracking-tight">
          Historical transparency only matters if you inspect the current bounded path, not the old score alone.
        </h2>
        <div class="space-y-4 text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
          <p>
            This March 11 baseline is useful because it shows where Rhumb started. The current question is whether today&apos;s narrower managed lane, credential path, and disclosed gaps are workable for your workflow.
          </p>
          <div class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2">
            <a data-rhumb-propagate href="/blog/we-scored-ourselves" class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-800 bg-navy/60 p-5 hover:border-emerald-400/30 transition-colors">
              <div class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-100">Read the fuller current self-assessment</div>
              <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-400">See the later 6.8/10 score, the disclosed gaps that still remain, and the current fit boundary.</p>
            </a>
            <a data-rhumb-propagate href="/blog/securing-keys-for-agents" class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-800 bg-navy/60 p-5 hover:border-emerald-400/30 transition-colors">
              <div class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-100">Inspect key containment before you widen authority</div>
              <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-400">The credential boundary matters more than the historical score once an agent can touch production state.</p>
            </a>
          </div>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3 pt-1">
            <a data-rhumb-propagate href="/blog/capability-first-agent-onboarding?rhumb_experiment=e004&rhumb_source=self-score-onboarding" class="px-5 py-3 rounded-xl border border-slate-700 text-sm text-slate-100 hover:border-emerald-400/50 hover:text-white transition-colors duration-200">
              See capability-first onboarding
            </a>
            <a data-rhumb-propagate href="/start-managed-execution?rhumb_experiment=e004&rhumb_source=self-score-direct" class="px-5 py-3 rounded-xl bg-emerald-400 text-navy font-display font-semibold text-sm hover:bg-emerald-300 transition-colors duration-200">
              Start managed execution
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="mt-10 rounded-[28px] border border-slate-800 bg-surface/70 p-6">
        <div class="text-[11px] font-mono uppercase tracking-[0.24em] text-slate-500 mb-3">Gap inspection</div>
        <div class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2">
          <a href="/blog/remote-mcp-production-readiness-checklist" class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-800 bg-navy/60 p-5 hover:border-slate-700 transition-colors">
            <div class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-100">Remote MCP Production Readiness Checklist</div>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-400">Use the live readiness checklist to judge whether bounded execution is good enough before you expand scope.</p>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/read-only-mcp-trust-class" class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-800 bg-navy/60 p-5 hover:border-slate-700 transition-colors">
            <div class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-100">Read-Only MCP Trust Class</div>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-400">A narrower authority class is often the honest first answer while sandbox and credential gaps still exist.</p>
          </a>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="mt-12" data-section="fleet-follow-through">
        <div class="rounded-[28px] border border-slate-800 bg-surface/70 p-6">
          <div class="mb-3 text-[11px] font-mono uppercase tracking-[0.24em] text-slate-500">Fleet follow-through</div>
          <h2 class="mb-3 font-display text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-slate-100">
            The old score only becomes useful when you inspect the live operator constraints too
          </h2>
          <p class="mb-5 leading-relaxed text-slate-300">
            Historical transparency is useful because it shows the starting point, not because the number stands alone. The real production read is what breaks inside loops, how shared provider budgets stay contained across agents, and whether credential scope survives the path from first demo to live execution. These three pages make that current-state read explicit.
          </p>
          <div class="grid gap-3 sm:grid-cols-3">
            <a href="/blog/llm-apis-agent-loops" class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-800 bg-navy/60 p-4 transition-colors hover:border-slate-700">
              <div class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-100">LLM APIs in Agent Loops</div>
              <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-400">What fails after the scorecard, once the agent starts chaining retries, tools, and provider calls unattended.</p>
            </a>
            <a href="/blog/agent-fleet-rate-limit-design" class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-800 bg-navy/60 p-4 transition-colors hover:border-slate-700">
              <div class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-100">Designing Agent Fleets That Survive Rate Limits</div>
              <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-400">How the bounded path still needs budget governors once more than one workflow shares the same provider rail.</p>
            </a>
            <a href="/blog/api-credentials-agent-fleets" class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-800 bg-navy/60 p-4 transition-colors hover:border-slate-700">
              <div class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-100">API Credentials in Autonomous Agent Fleets</div>
              <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-400">Why the real trust test is whether scope, expiry, and rotation stay legible after the first working call.</p>
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Related -->
      <section class="mt-12">
        <h2 class="font-display font-semibold text-lg text-slate-100 mb-4">
          Related
        </h2>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <a
            href="/blog/aag-framework"
            class="block bg-surface border border-slate-800 rounded-lg p-5 hover:border-amber/30 transition-colors"
          >
            <span class="text-xs font-mono text-amber uppercase tracking-widest">
              Framework
            </span>
            <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-slate-100 mt-2">
              The WCAG for AI Agents
            </h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 mt-1">
              Agent Accessibility Guidelines &mdash; a three-level framework for
              making web apps work for autonomous AI agents.
            </p>
          </a>
          <a
            href="/blog/payments-for-agents"
            class="block bg-surface border border-slate-800 rounded-lg p-5 hover:border-amber/30 transition-colors"
          >
            <span class="text-xs font-mono text-amber uppercase tracking-widest">
              Tool Autopsy
            </span>
            <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-slate-100 mt-2">
              Why Stripe Scores 8.1 and PayPal Scores 4.9 for AI Agents
            </h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 mt-1">
              We scored 6 payment APIs on how well they work for AI
              agents. The most popular one scored worst.
            </p>
          </a>
        </div>
      </section>
    </article>
  </div>
  <script is:inline>
    (() => {
      if (typeof window === "undefined") return;
      const params = new URLSearchParams(window.location.search);
      const experiment = params.get("rhumb_experiment");
      const source = params.get("rhumb_source");
      const parentSource = params.get("rhumb_parent_source");
      if (!experiment && !source && !parentSource) return;

      document.querySelectorAll("a[data-rhumb-propagate]").forEach((link) => {
        const href = link.getAttribute("href");
        if (!href) return;

        const url = new URL(href, window.location.origin);
        if (experiment && !url.searchParams.has("rhumb_experiment")) {
          url.searchParams.set("rhumb_experiment", experiment);
        }
        if (source) {
          url.searchParams.set("rhumb_parent_source", source);
        }
        if (parentSource) {
          url.searchParams.set("rhumb_grandparent_source", parentSource);
        }

        link.setAttribute("href", `${url.pathname}${url.search}${url.hash}`);
      });
    })();
  </script>
</Layout>
